ActuatorPowers
version=1
nRows=8125
nColumns=3
inDegrees=no

This file contains either the forces, speeds, or powers developed
by the actuators of a model during a simulation.

An actuator force is a generalized force, meaning that it can be either a force (N) or a torque (Nm).

An actuator speed is the rate at which an actuator shortens. Depending on the actuator,
a speed can be either a translational speed (m/s) or an angular speed (deg/s or rad/s).

An actuator power (Watts) is the rate at which an actuator does work.  Positive power means
that the actuator is delivering energy to the model; negative power means that the actuator
is absorbing energy from the model.

Units are S.I. units (second, meters, Newtons, ...)
If the header above contains a line with 'inDegrees', this indicates whether rotational values are in degrees (yes) or radians (no).

endheader
